  "prompt": "Can I get into the CSE in VIT Chennai at 70+ marks?",
  "response": "Admission to VIT Chennai, particularly for the Computer Science and Engineering (CSE) program, is highly competitive. The selection process primarily involves the VIT Engineering Entrance Exam (VITEEE). \n\nWhile scoring 70+ marks in VITEEE can be a decent score, the cut-off marks for CSE tend to be higher due to its popularity and demand. Historically, students who secure top ranks in VITEEE are often selected for the CSE program. Therefore, the exact cut-off can vary each year based on the number of applicants, difficulty level of the exam, and overall performance of candidates.\n\nIt would be best to aim for a higher score to increase your chances of securing admission to the CSE program at VIT Chennai. Additionally, keep an eye on the official announcements from VIT regarding the cut-off marks and admission criteria for the most accurate information.",
